The heat required for the endothermic reaction of the O2 uncoupling is provided by concentrated solar power. A suitable design for the collectors is a heliostat field, which consists of an array of planar mirrors (Barlev et al. 2011). The mirrors are reflecting the incident sunlight focused on the receiver, which is located on the top of a tower in the centre of the array (Barlev et al. 2011). The solar power heat flow, Q̇CSP\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
